{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Recent advancements in facial emotion recognition have been significantly influenced by deep learning algorithms.",
    "Jain et al. [12] introduced single deep neural network (DNN) incorporating convolution layers and deep residual blocks.",
    "Lopes et al. [13], in a similar vein, presented a multiple CNN framework, complemented by a specialized image pre-processing stage for emotion recognition.The application of FER in dynamic environments was addressed by Jain et al.",
    "[14] through the deployment of a hybrid convolution-recurrent neural network technique.",
    "A comparative analysis was conducted by Sajjanhar et al. [15] on the performance of pre-trained facial recognition algorithms, Visual Geometry Group (VGG)-facial and Inception, both initially developed for object detection."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
